cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.PF 

This paper is about a technique for detecting heavy flows in network traffic, which is a topic in network measurement and analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a new data structure for this purpose, which involves algorithms and data structures, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely category. The paper also discusses the performance and accuracy of the proposed technique, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed technique on programmable switches, which could fall under cs.PF (Performance).
